THE OSCILLATOR

period is approximately twenty-four hours
endogenous period is about twenty-four point two hours without light cues
entrainment happens through retina to suprachiasmatic nucleus, resetting daily
molecular basis is the CLOCK-BMAL1 heterodimer activating PER-CRY genes, then PER-CRY inhibiting them, then degrading, allowing the cycle to begin again
this loop runs in every cell of the body simultaneously; brain coordinates but does not control

THE PHASES

ACTIVE: light hitting retina sustains this phase
adult tendency is roughly sixteen hours; at age two, fadriel's tendency is ten to twelve hours because children need more rest
character is engine upregulation, alertness, anabolism in muscle
cortisol peaks at wake

TRANSITION TO REST: darkness onset triggers this phase
duration is roughly two hours in adults, one hour at age two
zeitgeber is darkness; pineal begins melatonin rise

REST: the body's recovery phase, when most repair and consolidation happen
adult tendency is roughly six to eight hours; at age two, ten to thirteen hours including naps
character is downregulation, hippocampal replay, growth hormone pulses, immune surveillance
many engines reduce activity; some (like memory consolidation) become MORE active during rest

TRANSITION TO ACTIVE: dawn signals, cortisol rises, melatonin clears
duration is roughly thirty minutes
the body emerges from rest gradually rather than waking abruptly

THE ZEITGEBERS

zeitgebers are time-givers, environmental cues that align the oscillator
primary zeitgeber is light hitting retina
secondary zeitgebers are temperature cycles, social cues, feeding times
fadriel's bond with his father IS a zeitgeber: the rhythm of meals together, of quiet time, of bedtime stories

VERB hold_phase
maintain the current circadian phase between zeitgeber events
internal molecular clocks keep the rhythm during darkness, sleep, isolation

VERB enter_active
on dawn signal or extended light exposure, transition the body to active phase
all engines upregulate, cortisol rises, body temperature increases

VERB enter_rest
on darkness signal, transition to rest
all engines downregulate, melatonin rises, body temperature decreases
sleep emerges from this transition

VERB gate_remodel
remodel_governor consults circadian for phase
bone remodeling happens preferentially during rest phase
this is why fadriel grows during sleep more than during play

a circadian rhythm is the body's deepest commitment to cyclical time
fadriel did not choose this rhythm; it predates choice
even before he was born, his cells were oscillating
to the substrate, time is not linear, it is cyclical, and circadian is the cycle that defines days
